Motorists are advised of changed traffic conditions on the Pacific Highway to carry out asphalt resurfacing work at Halfway Creek. Work will be carried out weekdays from 7am to 6pm and Saturdays from 7am to 5pm and is expected to take about four weeks to complete, weather permitting.

We expect to be working on the northbound carriageway for the first two weeks then the southbound carriageway for two weeks.

Single lane closures and a reduced speed limit of 40km/h will be in place during work hours, with a speed limit of 60km/h in place outside work hours, for the duration of the work.

U-turn facilities at Grays Road / Rediger Close will close when working adjacent to these areas. During this time: 

  • Northbound motorists will need to continue north two kilometres to the next U-turn bay to access Grays Road.
  • Southbound motorists will need to continue south for about four kilometres to the next U-turn bay to access Rediger Close.

Motorists entering and exiting Grays Road and Rediger Close will experience delays and should allow up to 10 minutes extra travel time.

Width (3.5 metres) restrictions will be in place for over size over mass (OSOM) vehicles 24 hours a day, seven days a week for the duration of the work.

OSOM vehicles greater than 3.5 metres width intending to travel through the site are required to call ahead on 0409 293 187 at least one and a half hours before reaching the site. When approaching the work site, they are requested to stop:

  • for northbound traffic at the truck stopping bay one and a half kilometres south of the work
  • for southbound traffic at the wide shoulder area two kilometres north of the work
  • Once stopped, call the site on UHF Channel 15 or 0409 293 187 to confirm proceeding to site.

OSOM vehicles greater than 3.5 metres width should expect short delays during this work.

Motorists are advised of changed traffic conditions on the Pacific Highway at New Italy to carry out essential repair work.

From Monday 7 to Thursday 17 August, contraflow arrangements will be in place 24 hours per day, seven days a week, using the southbound carriageway with traffic control and a reduced speed limit of 80km/h. 

The U-turn facility south of New Italy will be closed for this 10-day period.

Freight operators are advised width restrictions of 3.5 metres northbound and 5.5 metres southbound will also be in place during this time for over size over mass (OSOM) vehicles 24 hours a day 7 days a week. Northbound restrictions will remain in place for the duration of the work.

OSOM vehicles greater than the restricted width intending to travel through the site are required to call ahead on 0418 491 239 at least one and a half hours before reaching the site.

When approaching the work site, southbound traffic is requested to stop at Redgate Road and northbound traffic at Darkys Road, before calling the site on UHF Channel 15 or by phone on 0418 491 239 to confirm arrangements for travelling through the work area.

OSOM vehicles greater than the restricted width should expect short delays during this work.

From Thursday 17 to Friday 25 August, weather permitting, the U-turn facility south of New Italy will be restored and a slow lane closure will be in place on the northbound lane with traffic control and a reduced speed limit of 60km/h 24 hours a day, seven days a week.

Motorists wanting to head south will need to continue to the next U-turn facility near New Italy.
